2007-10-20 21:30  kelnos

	* src/menu.c, src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c, src/xfdesktop-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon.h, src/xfdesktop-special-file-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-volume-icon.c, src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon.c: redo menu system, part 2. the
	  desktop context menus with file icons and
	  window icons is now a lot more usable. for both window icons and
	  file icons,
	  when you right click on an icon, you get the icon's context menu,
	  with
	  the xfce root menu in a submenu. for file icons, if you right
	  click on
	  the desktop, you get the desktop's context menu (with 'create
	  launcher' etc.)
	  with the xfce root menu as a submenu.

2007-10-20 20:36  kelnos

	* configure.ac.in, modules/menu/desktop-menu.c: jannis made it
	  possible to clean up the vtable, so let's do that.
	  requires newer version of libxfce4menu

2007-10-20 19:46  kelnos

	* modules/menu/desktop-menu.c: no need to clear XfceMenu monitor
	  vtable

2007-10-20 19:21  kelnos

	* src/menu.c, src/windowlist.c: use correct function prototype,
	  even tho it doesn't really matter in this
	  case

2007-10-20 19:10  kelnos

	* ChangeLog, common/desktop-menu-stub.c,
	  common/desktop-menu-stub.h, menueditor/Makefile.am,
	  menueditor/dummy_icon.h, menueditor/menueditor-main-window.c,
	  modules/menu/Makefile.am, modules/menu/desktop-menu-private.h,
	  modules/menu/desktop-menu.c, modules/menu/desktop-menu.h,
	  modules/menu/dummy_icon.h, src/Makefile.am, src/main.c,
	  src/main.h, src/menu.c, src/menu.h, src/windowlist.c,
	  src/windowlist.h, src/xfce-desktop.c, src/xfce-desktop.h,
	  src/xfdesktop-marshal.list: Redo how the menu system works so i
	  can support multiple menus on the
	  desktop propery. Instead of the old method, where main.c watched
	  the
	  desktop for mouse clicks, not XfceDesktop does that, and emits
	  two new
	  signals: populate-root-menu and populate-secondary-root-menu.
	  Handlers
	  of these get passed a GtkMenu, which they should fill with menu
	  items.
	  They can (optionally) check to see if the passed GtkMenu already
	  has
	  menu items in it (put there by another handler) and put menu
	  items in
	  a submenu of the passed item.
	  
	  This cleaned up interfaces quite a bit and moved code to some
	  more sane
	  locations. The semi-downside of this is that now XfceDesktopMenu
	  needs
	  to generate a GtkMenu tree from the XfceMenu every time the menu
	  has
	  popped up. Performance doesn't seem to be hurt too much on my
	  system,
	  but it might be a problem for some really slow old hardware (but
	  hopefully
	  not). The upside is that the full GtkMenu tree isn't kept around
	  in
	  RAM all the time.
	  
	  End-user behavior hasn't changed yet, but this will let me
	  properly fix the
	  context menu for the desktop when file icons are enabled.

2007-10-20 16:47  kelnos

	* src/Makefile.am, src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c, src/xfdesktop-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-marshal.list: auto-generate marshalling functions

2007-10-20 16:46  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c, src/xfdesktop-file-utils.c: *
	  semi-fix a problem with loading file icons
	  * fix a spurious warning that gcc 4.2 generates for no apparent
	  reason

2007-10-06 17:00  mmassonnet

