	* src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c, src/xfdesktop-file-utils.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-file-utils.h, src/xfdesktop-special-file-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-volume-icon.c: change the cursor to the hourglass
	  while invoking some dbus methods

2006-11-04 10:55  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-regular-file-icon.c, src/xfdesktop-volume-icon.c:
	  this should fix the crash when dragging thunar's 'file system'
	  icon to the
	  desktop (bug 2470), but it doesn't because thunar-vfs craps out
	  when you try
	  to do that, for no reason i can see. if benny wants to keep it
	  this way, i'll
	  have to add a workaround :-p

2006-11-04 10:28  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c, src/xfdesktop-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon.h, src/xfdesktop-regular-file-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-special-file-icon.c, src/xfdesktop-volume-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon.c: remove
	  XfdesktopIcon::is_drop_dest().
	  XfdesktopIcon::get_allowed_drop_actions()
	  serves the same purpose (0 for FALSE, something else for TRUE).
	  implement
	  all the get_allowed_drag_actions() and get_allowed_drop_actions()
	  in the
	  various XfdesktopIcon subclasses. things are a lot more sane now.

2006-11-04 08:55  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c, src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon-view.h, src/xfdesktop-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon.h, src/xfdesktop-regular-file-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-special-file-icon.c, src/xfdesktop-volume-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.c, src/xfdesktop-window-icon.c:
	  first step to making DnD much less sucky and unmaintainable.
	  XfdesktopIcon
	  has two more vfuncs: get_allowed_drag_actions() and
	  get_allowed_drop_actions()
	  to help determining what kinds of drags and drops are allowed for
	  a particular
	  icon. XfdesktopIconView has lost the set_allow_overlapping_drops
	  property,
	  because it's just really not necessary.
	  
	  most of xfdesktop_icon_view_drag_motion() has been redone, and it
	  now looks
	  a lot cleaner and makes way more sense than before.
	  
	  no, the multiple DnD bug still isn't fixed. but now it should be
	  easier to
	  fix it.

