2006-02-06 09:20  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c, src/xfdesktop-icon-view.h,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.c: ok, that was wrong. handle
	  icon selection by adding some signals to
	  XfdesktopIconView. it's more efficient this way anyway, since
	  it's one signal
	  per view instead of per icon

2006-02-06 09:07  kelnos

	* src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.c, src/xfdesktop-window-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon.h: * fix crash; each icon_workspaces[]
	  element will always be valid now
	  * handle the selected icon when moving between workspaces

2006-02-06 08:56  kelnos

	* src/Makefile.am, src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-file-icon-manager.h, src/xfdesktop-file-icon.h,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon-view-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon-view-manager.h, src/xfdesktop-icon-view.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-icon-view.h, src/xfdesktop-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon-manager.h, src/xfdesktop-window-icon.c,
	  src/xfdesktop-window-icon.h: everything should compile ok now,
	  though the view doesn't quite work yet.
	  i've left out the changes in xfce-desktop.c so the old icon view
	  will still
	  work properly.
	  
	  here's what we have:
	  
	  * XfceDesktop: this is the same XfceDesktop from before, but all
	  the window
	  icon stuff has been ripped out, aside from a few setup hooks.
	  * XfdesktopIconView: a widget that sits on top of XfceDesktop. it
	  doesn't
	  have its own GdkWindow, but draws on XfceDesktop's. its job is to
	  keep
	  track of and draw XfdesktopIcons on the desktop. it doesn't know
	  or care
	  what they are. it just knows they have a pixbuf and label. this
	  code is
	  most of what was ripped out of XfceDesktop.
	  * XfdesktopIcon: a GInterface that describes an icon on the
	  desktop
	  * XfdesktopWindowIcon: an implementation of XfdesktopIcon that
	  knows stuff
	  about application windows.
	  * XfdesktopFileIcon: an (incomplete) implementation of
	  XfdesktopIcon that knows
	  stuff about files and folders.
	  * XfdesktopIconViewManager: a GInterface that provides a
	  "manager" for an
	  XfdesktopIconView. this manager will be owned by its associated
	  XfdesktopIconView and can control what is displayed via
	  XfdesktopIconView's
	  API.
	  * XfdesktopWindowIconManager: an implementation of
	  XfdesktopIconViewManager
	  that knows about application windows and what to do with them
	  when they
	  change state. it uses XfdesktopWindowIcon to keep track of
	  windows.
	  * XfdesktopFileIconManager: an (incomplete) implementation of
	  XfdesktopIconViewManager that knows about files in a directory
	  and how to
	  manipulate them.

2006-02-05 17:53  yuvaltanny

